ie.gmit.sw.base

Class ConcurrentCounterHashMap<K>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ie.gmit.sw.base.ConcurrentCounterHashMap<K>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of object counted by this counter
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CounterMap<K>, Identifiable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class ConcurrentCounterHashMap<K>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable, CounterMap<K>
    Concurrent implementation of CounterMap using a HashMap. Allow all operations needed for count shingle.

    Basically a hash map that link objects with his count, when a new object is counted, his mapped value will be increased by 1.

    When new objects are added they will be keep on a key set and his count set to 1.

    Author:
    Jose I. Retamal
